<HEADER>
A7077 &Cx1f; tad-z
u e BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE29     06-28 0571
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE29-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    WRESTLING GRAPEVINE: News, gossip from the industry
 &HT;    By John Allen
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   After being on the shelf for months with an arm injury, Goldberg
has given the WCW another reason to look for someone else to
feature after he re-injured his arm at ``Nitro'' Monday. He was
unable to work the next night's ``Thunder'' show, but is scheduled
to return to the ring for this week's ``Nitro.''
</P>
<P>
   Seems like the same problems that kept Goldberg's NFL career
from taking off (injuries) are keeping him from maintaining his
status as WCW's top draw.
</P>
<P>
   _ An injury in preparation for her ``Thunder'' match will also
keep Major Gunns out of the ring. She and Paisley were to face off.
The match is now on hold.
</P>
<P>
   _ It looks as though Raven could be a next ECW star to fly the
coop. Reports on the internet say Raven has had talks with WWF.
Raven, who wrestled for WCW after a lengthy run with ECW could sign
with the WWF in September.
</P>
<P>
   _ Former Raven protege Stevie Richards has returned from a foot
injury with a new gimmick for the WWF. He is expected to fight for
more censorship of the WWF's profane, sexually explicted ways.
</P>
<P>
   _ The 'Stone Cold' Steve Austin watch is warming up thanks to
some promotion of the WWF's July 23 pay-per-view, ``Fully Loaded.''
Promotional posters have Austin on them and the pay-per-view
Website (ppv.com). They read: ``Luck, chance ... those words have
no place in `Stone Cold' Steve Austin's vocabulary. He relies on
skill and fortitude to eliminate those who stand in his way. When
`Stone Cold' rolls the dice they're guaranteed to come up snake
eyes every time.'' While all promotional info says as usual that
the card is subject to change, it is interesting that Austin is the
focal point.
</P>
<P>
   _ Speaking of ``Fully Loaded,'' all signs point to the Rock,
Kurt Angle, Triple H and the Undertaker being involved in the main
event. It would be strange for the WWF to have another four
wrestler match as the pay-per-view main event, but it keeps a lot
of story options alive. The biggest would be a change of Triple H
from a heel to a face and Angle becoming the focal point of the
McMahon faction.
</P>
<P>
   _ Despite a tombstone piledriver by Kane on Triple H in the
``King of the Ring'' pay-per-view, the WWF is limiting the use of
such moves that could cause neck tauma.
</P>
<P>
   _ Head tauma is what Val Venis' valet Trish Stratus was feeling
after receiving a powerbomb from Chyna Monday night. The WWF cut to
a quick commerical as soon as the match between Venis and Chyna's
main man Eddy Guerrero ended. Stratus suffered a concussion from
the whiplash effect of the move and did not go to ringside with her
tag team T&AMP;A later in the show. While Stratus continued to work
with Venis and T&AMP;A, expect her to spilt from T&AMP;A before the end of
the summer.
</P>
<P>
   _ Richard Reid Flair, father of Ric Flair, died Sunday at the
age of 81. Ric Flair, the 15-time world heavyweight champion, said,
``I hope I can be half the man my father was. He was successful in
everything he tried, and very unassuming. He was just the greatest,
most honest guy I've ever met.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Latest Monday night rating have the WWF with a 6.4 to 2.8
advantage over WCW. Although not the widest gaps, it continues to
be no contest between pro wrestling's top two organizations.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
