as one of the men responsible for mapping the human genome, Dr.
Craig Venter wrote about the possibility of genetically engineering
a man with bird wings. That's the image most people have of angels.
The idea of a scientific breakthrough that can put God out of
business has to disturb some people. (Nethaway, Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
