<P>
   CONSUMER NEWS
</P>
<P>
   BUYER'S-EDGE _ FOOD-FOURTH _ How to set the scene for a
firecracker of a party for 10 for under $100. We'll tell readers
how to roll out the red, white and blue for a last-minute
neighborhood potluck and watermelon cutting _ guests will bring
thier favorite cool summer salads and host will provide the melon.
Money will be spent on table decorations, paperware, cups, maybe a
festive lemonade pitcher, little American flags and small
citronella candles that will be take-home party favors. (MJohnson,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
