</P>
<P>
   FOOD-SWEETTEA _ As much as the South is known for sweet tea,
it's really kind of hard to find a good glass. Here's how to make
proper sweet tea. (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 16.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-REUNIONS _ Home-baked ham and store-bought chicken; simple
deviled eggs and fancy baked beans; elaborate coconut cake and pure
peach cobbler all crowded a 30-foot island at the Griffin City Park
for the Jackson-Moore Family Reunion. We take a look at family
reunion potlucks. (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   Recipes of family reunion favorites from Georgia families and
families from other states. (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
80.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-RECIPESWAP _A weekly recipe exchange column. This week:
Salmon Pate. (Langhenry, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-CYBERSPICE _ A weekly column looking at the plethora of
recipes on the Internet. (Parham, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FOOD PAGE
</P>
