surivior of the Bataan Death March who lives in Boca Raton, Fla.,
recieved a Purple Heart for his service during World War II.
(O'Dell, Cox News Service). 15.
</P>
<P>
   SYRIA-CLASSICCARS _ DAMASCUS, Syria _ Between the centuries old
mosques and the Roman ruins, Syrians like Abdel Malek Sheikho keep
history rolling down the street. Sheikho screeches the tires of his
bright red 1951 DeSoto Delux as he weaves through the crowded
streets. It's powered by a Chevy engine and has the occasional
Cadillac part inside. And, he's got a large poster of the late
Syrian President Hafez Assad in the windshield. At the garage zone
on the edge of the capital, workers hammer the chrome trim around
the fins of a 1959 Buick. They scramble for parts to fit the motley
fleet brought in for repairs. They polish up a Bel Air station
wagon, a 1963 Mercedes, old Skoda's and Fiats. A closed economy and
high taxes make it hard to get cars in Syria, so drivers and
mechanics keep the old ones running. (Kaplow, Cox News Service).
25. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
