<P>
   CHAIR-BACK _ Reach back. Slowly run your hand along the row of
buttons, the metal studs. Gently caress the shoulders and
curvaceous sides. Before you know it, you will have ``undressed'' a
secret to designing sofas and chairs for today's large rooms.
Furniture, instead of hugging the walls, is being ``floated'' more
often these days to the center of the room to form a cozy
arrangement conducive to conversation or watching the tube. As that
occurs, consumers are suddenly noticing bare backs and sides.
(Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.) WITH PHOTOS.
