   SCIENCE-MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   SPACE-STATION _ The Russians call it ``Zvezda,'' or Star. To
NASA, the 43-foot-long cylinder is simply ``the service module'' -
the most crucial component of the costliest space project in
history. By any name, the capsule now undergoing final checks is a
milestone in the development of the $60 billion International Space
Station. As NASA officials hold a news conference Wednesday to
announce the launch of Zvezda, in early July, critics say the
delays in Zvezda's lofting _ and in the space station project
itself _are beginning to make NASA's management of the project look
like to a ``Keystone cops'' movie. (Toner, Atlanta
Journal-ConstituTION). 45.
</P>
