<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FOOD-VANITYPLATES-2ndTake-TEX </SLUG>
 
UNDATED: CopyKat.com 
<TEXT>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   TURKEY (OR CHICKEN) TETRAZZINI
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8
</P>
<P>
   5 tablespoons butter, divided
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons flour
</P>
<P>
   2 cups chicken broth
</P>
<P>
   1 cup heavy cream
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons dry sherry or Madeira
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese, divided
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon black pepper
</P>
<P>
   3/4 pound medium mushrooms, wiped clean and thinly sliced
</P>
<P>
   3 medium scallions, trimmed and thinly sliced
</P>
<P>
   1 pound spaghetti, cooked al dente according to package
directions and drained well
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup diced canned pimentos
</P>
<P>
   4 cups diced cooked turkey or chicken
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Lightly coat 13-by-9-by-2-inch
baking dish with nonstick cooking spray and set aside.
</P>
<P>
   Melt 3 tablespoons butter in medium heavy saucepan over moderate
heat. Blend in flour, add broth, then cook, stirring constantly,
until thickened and smooth _ about 3 minutes. Mix in cream, sherry,
1/4 cup Parmesan and pepper. Cook and stir 2 minutes, then remove
from heat.
</P>
<P>
   Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter in large heavy skillet over
moderate heat. Add mushrooms and scallions and stir-fry until limp
_ about 3 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Toss spaghetti in large bowl with sauce, mushroom mixture,
pimentos and turkey. Transfer to prepared baking dish and scatter
remaining 1/2 cup Parmesan evenly over all.
</P>
<P>
   Bake, uncovered, until bubbling and brown _ 20-25 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 501 calories, 21 grams fat, 48
grams carbohydrates, 29 grams protein, 97 milligrams cholesterol,
509 milligrams sodium, 37 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The American Century Cookbook'' by Jean Anderson (Potter,
$35)
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   PEACH MELBA
</P>
<P>
   Serves 6
</P>
<P>
   Melba sauce:
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon cornstarch
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup orange juice
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups fresh raspberries, or 10-ounce package frozen
raspberries, thawed Assembly:
</P>
<P>
   3 fresh peaches
</P>
<P>
   1 quart nonfat frozen vanilla yogurt
</P>
<P>
   Combine sugar, cornstarch and orange juice in a small saucepan
over medium heat. Stir mixture until it becomes thick and bubbly.
Add raspberries and heat until warm. Remove sauce from heat and set
aside. Cut fresh peaches in half and remove pits.
</P>
<P>
   Place each half in glass dessert dish. Place a scoop of nonfat
vanilla yogurt in each half (about 1/4 cup). Top with Melba sauce
and serve immediately.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 137 calories, trace fat, 33
grams carbohydrates, 2 grams protein, 5 milligrams cholesterol, 45
milligrams sodium, 0 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ www.KetchumKitchen.com
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   PAVLOVA
</P>
<P>
   Serves 6-8
</P>
<P>
   4 egg whites at room temperature
</P>
<P>
   1 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon white vinegar
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon vanilla
</P>
<P>
   1/2 tablespoon cornstarch
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 250 degrees. Beat egg whites until they start to
form soft peaks. Gradually add sugar, beating constantly.
</P>
<P>
   Continue beating until mixture forms stiff peaks. Fold in
vinegar, vanilla and cornstarch. Mound meringue on cookie sheet.
Indent with back of spoon to form a bowl shape. Bake for 11/2
hours. Turn oven off and allow meringue to dry in cooling oven.
Place meringue on serving plate. Fill with fresh fruit and ice
cream, whipped cream or gelatin.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 139 calories, 3 grams fat, 26
grams carbohydrates, 3 grams protein, 106 milligrams cholesterol,
32 milligrams sodium, 16 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ www.virtualcities.com
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Box 1870, Fort Worth, Texas 76101. Or E-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
