<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RECIPES-BUNDY-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A FEW CALORIES, BUT WORTH IT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BEVERLY BUNDY 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   A couple of weeks ago, we ran a request for a salmon pie that a
reader remembered her mother making. I didn't receive any crusted
salmon pie recipes, but Gertie Prater of Paradise sent the cheese
bake, which includes salmon.
</P>
<P>
   Louise Veal of Burleson sent us one of her favorite cake recipes
just to share.
</P>
<P>
   And the last recipe is one from a news service. It's for all of
us who decided not to buy a new swimsuit this summer.
</P>
<P>
   CHEESY RICE BAKE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 6
</P>
<P>
   10-ounce can condensed cream of mushroom soup
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup milk
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoons chopped parsley
</P>
<P>
   2 cups cooked rice (about 2/3 cup uncooked rice)
</P>
<P>
   15-ounce can salmon, drained, flaked and picked over for bones
</P>
<P>
   1 cup cooked peas, drained
</P>
<P>
   1 cup shredded sharp cheese
</P>
<P>
   In large bowl, combine soup, milk and parsley; stir to blend.
Stir in rice, salmon and peas. Turn mixture into 10-by-6-inch
baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
</P>
<P>
   Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until heated through.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 321 calories, 14 grams fat, 27
grams carbohydrates, 21 grams protein, 44 milligrams cholesterol,
810 milligrams sodium, 38 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   A WINE CAKE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 12-16
</P>
<P>
   18-ounce box yellow butter cake mix
</P>
<P>
   Small box instant vanilla pudding
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup wine (Concord grape)
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup vegetable oil
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup milk
</P>
<P>
   4 eggs
</P>
<P>
   1 cup chopped nuts
</P>
<P>
   Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured
bundt pan. Cook at 350 degrees for 1 hour. Leave cake in pan when
done, and pour the following icing over it.
</P>
<P>
   Icing:
</P>
<P>
   1 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 stick butter
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup wine
</P>
<P>
   Cook on top of stove. Let it boil for about 10 minutes, or until
it cooks down low; take off stove and pour over cake still in pan.
Let cake cool for 30 minutes, then remove from pan and serve. Cake
can be frozen.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 414 calories, 4 grams fat, 49
grams carbohydrates, 4 grams protein, 70 milligrams cholesterol,
345 milligrams sodium, 49 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   DEATH BY CHOCOLATE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 16-20
</P>
<P>
   2 boxes brownie mix
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup coffee-flavored liqueur (such as Kahlua)
</P>
<P>
   Two 4-serving size packages chocolate pudding mix
</P>
<P>
   16-ounce container frozen whipped topping, defrosted
</P>
<P>
   8 Heath bars (or similar candy), crushed
</P>
<P>
   1 cup chopped pecans
</P>
<P>
   Bake brownies as directed on the package. When cooled slightly,
poke holes in the top with a fork and pour the liqueur over them.
When the brownies are thoroughly soaked, crumble and place in
serving dish with tall sides. Prepare chocolate pudding as
directed. Put half the pudding on top of the brownie layer. Add
half the whipped topping, then half the candy. Layer on remaining
pudding, followed by remaining candy and whipped topping. Sprinkle
pecans over the top.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 465 calories, 19 grams fat, 71
grams carbohydrates, 4 grams protein, 3 milligrams cholesterol, 395
milligrams sodium, 37 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Box 1870, Fort Worth, Texas 76101. Or E-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)  &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
