   LITTLE-ROCK-CULTURE (Little Rock, Ark.) _ Visitors to this small
Southern city (metropolitan population: 570,000) are often struck
by the gap between its reputation as an intellectual backwater and
the reality of its cultural offerings: a nationally recognized
symphony, a civic ballet, a comprehensive university fine arts
department, two repertory theater companies and a small but
state-of-the-art performance center. By Steve Barnes.
