national Southern Baptist Convention, but doctrines adopted by the
body's conservatives this month have driven a deep wedge between
the state and national groups, moderate Baptist leaders say. Many
Texas Baptists are distressed over the revised Baptist Faith and
Message which they say exalts the Bible over Jesus. The independent
state convention may cut back on the more than $40 million it sends
annually to the national convention. By JIM JONES. Story has moved
