<P>
   FED-RATES (Washington0 _ The Federal Reserve voted Wednesday to
leave interest rates unchanged, giving itself more time to
determine whether the series of rate increases it has imposed over
the last year are slowing the economy sufficiently to avoid an
upturn in inflation. But the central bank warned that it could
start raising rates again as soon as its next meeting, on Aug. 22,
unless economic indicators in coming weeks provide assurance that
the red-hot pace of economic growth earlier this year has given way
to a more sustainable level that reduces the threat of an
inflationary spiral in wages and prices. By Richard W. Stevenson.
</P>
<P>
   PROVIDIAN-FRAUD (Washington) _ In a clear sign of the
government's attempt to crack down on deceptive lending practices,
a major credit-card company agreed Wednesday to reimburse its
customers at least $300 million for misleading and improperly
billing them. By David Leonhardt.
</P>
