has built the most powerful computer in history, Capable of 12.3
trillion operations per second, it is three times faster than the
world's most powerful computer now, and 1000 times more powerful
than the IBM ``Deep Blue'' computer that defeated world chess
champion Gary Kasparov in 1997. The new computer was built for the
U.S. Department of Energy to simulate nuclear explosions. (Glass,
Cox News Service).
