<P>
   AIRTRAN-ADS _ ATLANTA _ Are cheap airfares in the same league
with famous victories over tyranny? AirTran Airways suggests they
are _ in a lighthearted way _ in new television ads debuting next
week. One shows a lone business traveler on a tarmac facing down a
jetliner, a scene modeled after the famous shot from from the 1989
Tiananmen Square riots. Another re-creates Life magazine's famous
shot of a couple kissing in Times Square at the end of World War
II. It pitches AirTran's lack of weekend stay restrictions. The
airline's also rolling out a new tagline, ``Your airline has
arrived.'' (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13.
