financial performance Wednesday as economies around the world
continue to improve. The Atlanta-based beverage giant said it
expects case sales in the second quarter to increase 5 percent to 6
percent, compared with a lackluster 3.5 percent in the first
quarter. (Unger, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
