<P>
   DOTCOMFAILURE _ Okay, so it doesn't look as easy as it did six
months ago. But in the last year, a lot of people have quit their
jobs with dreams of hatching an Internet company, drowning in
venture capital, going public and retiring to a tropical island.
Easy money, right? Wrong. Most Internet startups never make it to
IPO, and there are as many reasons for that as there are goofy
Internet ideas, everything from the wrong business model to the
wrong management team. We talk to entrepreneurs whose dot-com
dreams went down what they learned and what they would do
differently if they got another chance. (Park, Austin
American-Statesman)
