<P>
   PROVIDIAN-FRAUD (Washington) _ In a clear sign of the
government's attempt to crack down on deceptive lending practices,
a major credit-card company agreed Wednesday to reimburse its
customers at least $300 million for misleading and improperly
billing them. By David Leonhardt.
